http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/The.label: ALK Negative
synonyms: Anaplastic Lymphoma Receptor Tyrosine Kinase Negative
defs: Indicates that expression of ALK has not been detected in a sample.

http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/The.label: ALK Gene
defs: This gene is involved in brain development and neuronal specificity.

http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/The.label: ALK Inhibitor
defs: Any agent that inhibits the activity of the receptor tyrosine kinase anaplastic lymphoma kinase (ALK).

http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/The.label: ALK Positive
defs: Indicates that ALK expression has been detected in a sample.

http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/The.label: ALK Protein Measurement
defs: The determination of the amount of ALK protein present in a sample.

http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/The.label: ALK Tyrosine Kinase Receptor
defs: ALK tyrosine kinase receptor (1620 aa, ~176 kDa) is encoded by the human ALK gene. This protein is involved in ligand binding, tyrosine phosphorylation and signal transduction.

http://ncicb.nci.nih.gov/xml/owl/EVS/The.label: ALK wt Allele
synonyms: ALK Receptor Tyrosine Kinase wt Allele
Anaplastic Lymphoma Receptor Tyrosine Kinase Gene
defs: Human ALK wild-type allele is located within 2p23 and is approximately 729 kb in length. This allele, which encodes ALK tyrosine kinase receptor protein, plays a role in brain development and exerts its effects on specific neurons in the nervous system.
